AB  - This paper develops an alternative method of deriving the ex-ante real rate of interest. Given assumptions regarding capital mobility and PPP, it is shown that in equilibrium the ex-ante real rate will be equalized across countries. Using cross-sectional regression techniques, this real rate can be estimated at each moment in time. Hence, it is possible to develop a time series of estimated real rates derived from cross-sectional regressions. This estimated real rate series is then used in time-series tests of the Fisher equation for the U.S.
